# The conversion of one data type into the other data type is known as type casting in python or type conversion in python.
# Python supports a wide variety of functions or methods like: intO, floato, stro, ordO, hex0, octO, tupleO, setO, listO, dict@, etc. for the type casting in python.
# Two Types of Typecasting:
# 1. Explicit Conversion (Explicit type casting in python)
# explicit done by us user or programmer 
# 2. Implicit Conversion (Implicit type casting in python).
# implicit is done by python

a = 20 
b = "12"  #string
c = a+int(b) #typecasting of b
f = a+ float(b)
print(type(b))
print(c)
print(f)
